The paper discusses the implementation of a neuro-fuzzy computing system on a memristor-crossbar structure, which falls under the category of hardware design for neural networks and fuzzy logic. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of memristive devices, which falls under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.EM (Electromagnetics), and cs.AR (Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the Hebbian learning rule and the ability to deal with large amounts of training data, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
